nations%20thus%20far.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20documents%20filed%20by%20the%20Justice%20Department%20shed%20light%20on%20just%20how%20far%20the%20White%20House%20and%20its%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-agencies-musk-doge-targeted-list-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20DOGE%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20gone%20in%20trying%20to%20cut%20probationary%20staff%20from%20the%20federal%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20declarations%20from%2018%20departments%20or%20agencies%2C%20officials%20said%20roughly%2025%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-orders-trump-reinstate-fired-probationary-federal-workers-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20workers%20had%20been%20terminated%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20government.%20Their%20disclosures%20are%20the%20largest%20insight%20yet%20into%20mass%20reductions%20that%20have%20become%20the%20signature%20focus%20of%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20first%20100%20days%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fnhq5E%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Probationary%20workers%20terminated%20under%20Trump%20administration%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22804%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAgency%20officials%20were%20required%20to%20file%20the%20declarations%20by%20Monday%20night%20in%20a%20legal%20case%20brought%20by%2020%20Democratic%20state%20attorneys%20general%20which%20allege%20that%20the%20mass%20firings%20were%20illegal.%20US%20District%20Court%20Judge%20James%20K.%20Bredar%20previously%20granted%20the%20attorneys%20general%20request%20to%20temporarily%20restrain%20the%20Trump%20administration%20from%20fully%20carrying%20out%20the%20terminations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20roughly%2025%2C000%20employees%20were%20put%20on%20administrative%20leave%20following%20their%20reinstatement%2C%20according%20to%20the%20filings.%20Some%20agencies%20have%20struggled%20to%20notify%20fired%20workers%20that%20they%20can%20come%20back.%20An%20IRS%20official%20said%20they%20had%20resorted%20to%20sending%20out%20certified%20mail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgency%20officials%20repeatedly%20warned%20that%20complying%20with%20Bredar's%20order%20could%20cause%20chaos%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20temporary%20block%20is%20lifted%20and%20the%20workers%20are%20fired%20again.%20Even%20if%20employees%20can%20return%20to%20work%2C%20many%20officials%20said%20in%20the%20filings%20any%20reinstated%20employee%20would%20have%20to%20go%20through%20the%20onboarding%20process%20again%2C%20requiring%20them%20to%20obtain%20security%20badges%2C%20complete%20training%2C%20and%20receive%20whatever%20equipment%20they%20needed%20for%20their%20jobs.%20Some%20of%20the%20agencies%20said%20they%20don't%20have%20enough%20office%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20targeted%20probationary%20employees%20with%20less%20than%20two%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20their%20roles%20as%20early%20as%20Inauguration%20Day.%20Probationary%20employees%20are%20typically%20easier%20to%20terminate%20since%20they%20lack%20some%20civil%20service%20protections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DOGE%20office%20was%20not%20directly%20responsible%20for%20the%20Office%20of%20Personnel%20Management%20memo%20that%20prompted%20agencies%20to%20review%20the%20status%20of%20their%20probationary%20employees.%20Tesla%20CEO%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20the%20de%20facto%20leader%20of%20the%20DOGE%20office%2C%20has%20championed%20mass%20firings%20and%20claimed%20credit%20for%20at%20least%20some%20efforts%20to%20reduce%20the%20size%20of%20government%2C%20namely%20the%20US%20Agency%20for%20International%20Development%20(USAID).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20agencies%20that%20have%20been%20hit%20the%20hardest%20so%20far%2C%20according%20to%20the%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%