ractors%20challenging%20the%20legal%20authority%20of%20the%20billionaire%20tapped%20by%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20to%20slash%20federal%20government%20spending%20and%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20argued%20that%20under%20the%20Appointments%20Clause%20of%20the%20US%20Constitution%2C%20Musk%20needed%20to%20be%20confirmed%20by%20the%20Senate%20in%20order%20to%20exercise%20his%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20agreed%2C%20saying%20that%20allowing%20Musk%20to%20continue%20to%20wield%20enormous%20power%20over%20the%20government%20%26quot%3Bwould%20open%20the%20door%20to%20an%20end-run%20around%20the%20Appointments%20Clause%26quot%3B%20and%20reduce%20it%20to%20%26quot%3Bnothing%20more%20than%20a%20technical%20formality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChuang%20said%20the%20actions%20by%20Musk%20and%20DOGE%20had%20violated%20the%20authority%20of%20Congress%20to%20decide%20when%20and%20how%20to%20close%20down%20USAID%2C%20where%20most%20of%20the%20workers%20have%20been%20placed%20on%20leave%20or%20fired%20since%20January.%20The%20agency%20was%20created%20by%20Congress%20in%201961.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecretary%20of%20State%20Marco%20Rubio%20said%20last%20week%20that%20the%20United%20States%20was%20cancelling%2083%20percent%20of%20programs%20at%20USAID%2C%20which%20distributes%20humanitarian%20aid%20around%20the%20world%2C%20with%20health%20and%20emergency%20programs%20in%20around%20120%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge's%20ruling%20was%20the%20latest%20legal%20setback%20to%20Trump's%20cost-cutting%20and%20government%20staff%20reduction%20drive.%20Another%20judge%20recently%20ordered%20the%20rehiring%20of%20thousands%20of%20probationary%20workers%20in%20multiple%20agencies%20who%20had%20been%20fired%20by%20Musk's%20DOGE.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChuang%20ordered%20that%20access%20to%20email%20and%20other%20electronic%20systems%20be%20reinstated%20to%20current%20USAID%20employees%20and%20contractors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20agency%20should%20also%20be%20allowed%20to%20reoccupy%20its%20Washington%20headquarters%20unless%20the%20court%20receives%20confirmation%20from%20the%20acting%20administrator%20of%20USAID%20or%20another%20authorized%20officer%20of%20the%20United%20States%20that%20the%20building%20is%20being%20permanently%20closed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20signed%20an%20executive%20order%20in%20January%20demanding%20a%20freeze%20on%20all%20US%20foreign%20aid%20to%20allow%20time%20to%20assess%20overseas%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742331360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2F6t23k98_elon-musk_625x300_03_March_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-court-orders-immediate-halt-to-elon-musk-shutdown-of-us-aid-agency-7955370%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20federal%20judge%20ordered%20an%20immediate%20halt%20on%20Tuesday%20to%20the%20shutdown%20of%20the%20main%20US%20aid%20agency%20by%20Elon%20Musk's%20Department%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%20(DOGE).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prince%20Harry's%20'heavily%20redacted'%20visa%20documents%20made%20public.%20He%20won't%20face%20deportation%20from%20US%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742331082000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-119177913%2Cimgsize-1094352.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fprince-harrys-heavily-redacted-visa-documents-made-public-he-wont-face-deportation-from-us%2Farticleshow%2F119177917.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F119177917.