https%3A%2F%2Fwww.embracepetinsurance.com%2Fwaterbowl%2Fauthor%2Fdr-liza-cahn%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Liza%20Cahn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20veterinarian%20and%20veterinary%20consultant%20for%20Embrace%20Pet%20Insurance.%20However%2C%20some%20cats%20%E2%80%94%20or%20their%20humans%20%E2%80%94%20may%20have%20different%20preferences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelow%2C%20we%20discuss%20clumping%20versus%20non-clumping%20litter%20so%20you%20can%20choose%20the%20best%20one%20for%20your%20household.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220fe81802-9385-4fde-8273-c93591c620ab%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22The%20differences%20between%20clumping%20and%20non-clumping%20cat%20litter%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20differences%20between%20clumping%20and%20non-clumping%20cat%20litter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECats%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20consistently%20use%20a%20litter%20box%20that%20is%20kept%20clean.%20Cahn%20recommends%20scooping%20clumping%20litter%20at%20least%20once%20a%20day%20and%20completely%20replacing%20the%20litter%20and%20deep-cleaning%20the%20box%20monthly.%20You%20may%20also%20need%20to%20add%20fresh%20litter%20between%20monthly%20cleanings.%20For%20non-clumping%20litter%2C%20Cahn%20says%20to%20scoop%20feces%20daily%20and%20replace%20the%20urine-soaked%20litter%20at%20least%20once%20a%20week.%20These%20guidelines%20aren't%20one-size-fits-all.%20Some%20cats%20may%20be%20pickier%2C%20preferring%20their%20litter%20box%20to%20be%20scooped%20more%20often%20or%20deep-cleaned%20more%20frequently.%20If%20your%20cat%20has%20a%20health%20condition%20that%20increases%20urination%2C%20such%20as%20kidney%20disease%2C%20you%20may%20need%20to%20clean%20their%20litter%20box%20more%20often.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClumping%20litter%20contains%20a%20binder%2C%20such%20as%20starch%2C%20guar%20gum%2C%20or%20bentonite%20clay.%20This%20helps%20it%20form%20solid%20clumps%20around%20liquid%20waste%2C%20making%20it%20possible%20to%20scoop%20out%20both%20liquid%20and%20solids.%20Clumping%20clay%20litter%20is%20widely%20popular%20among%20cats%20and%20their%20humans%20because%20cats%20prefer%20its%20sand-like%20texture%2C%20while%20people%20appreciate%20its%20affordability.%20There%20are%20also%20alternatives%20to%20clay%2C%20including%20corn%2C%20cassava%2C%20and%20tofu-based%20clumping%20litters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENon-clumping%20litter%20absorbs%20moisture%20without%20forming%20clumps%20and%20is%20made%20with%20materials%20such%20as%20pine%20pellets%2C%20shredded%20paper%2C%20or%20silica%20crystals.%20Each%20type%20requires%20a%20different%20approach%20to%20maintenance.%20For%20example%2C%20silica%20litter%20often%20requires%20stirring%20to%20prevent%20over-saturation%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-74876-20%26h%3Dbee5c9cdcefa84ef7464931f986e341f827d9cbd9b26919cf8de4ae591a44212%26postID%3D67d99499e45285883912df55%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Fclumping-vs-non-clumping-litter%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.rover.com%252Fblog%252Fdr-mikel-delgado%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMikel%20Delgado%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20consulting%20cat%20behavior%20expert%20for%20Rover%2C%20says%20stirring%20around%20dirty%20litter%20can%20worsen%20odors%20and%20change%20the%20texture.%20Scooping%20the%20wet%20silica%20crystals%20is%20usually%20ineffective%2C%20though%20soiled%20paper%20litter%20may%20be%20easier%20to%20scoop%20out.%20Pine%20pellets%20break%20down%20into%20sawdust%20when%20wet%2C%20and%20a%20sifting%20litter%20box%20can%20help%20separate%20fresh%20pellets%20from%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dea67ac3-ea08-463d-a672-3fbbe6d66e52%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Is%20clumping%20or%20non-clumping%20litter%20better%3F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20clumping%20or%20non-clumping%20litter%20better%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20types%20of%20litter%20have%20absorbent%2C%20odor-locking%20properties%2C%20but%20one%20might%20work%20better%20for%20your%20household%20than%20the%20other.%20Understanding%20the%20differences%20between%20clumping%20and%20non-clumping%20cat%20litter%20is%20important%20so%20you%20can%20choose%20appropriately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f1ea1e51-7952-4308-a92f-276d203f2972%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Clumping%20cat%20litter%20pros%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EClumping%20cat%20litter%20pros%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECost-effective%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EClumping%20litter%20isn't%20always%20cheaper%20than%20non-clumping%20options%20on%20a%20bag-to-bag%20basis%2C%20but%20it%20tends%20to%20last%20longer.%20Scooping%20out%20solid%20and%20liquid%20waste%20keeps%20the%20litter%20fresher%2C%20so%20you%20only%20need%20to%20completely%20replace%20it%20about%20every%20three%20to%20four%20weeks%20or%20sooner%2C%20depending%20on%20your%20cat's%20preference%20for%20litter%20box%20hygeine.%20If%20you%20notice%20the%20litter%20level%20drops%20too%20low%20between%20deep%20cleanings%2C%20you%20may%20need%20to%20top%20it%20off%20with%20fresh%20litter%20%E2%80%94%20cats%20prefer%20a%20litter%20depth%20of%201.5%20inches%20or%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETexture%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECats%20often%20prefer%20clumping%20litter%20because%20its%20texture%20resembles%20the%20sand%20or%20dirt%20they%20would%20dig%20in%20outdoors%2C%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cityvet.com%2Flocation%2Fcharlotte-uptown%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Elena%20Shirley%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20lead%20veterinarian%20and%20partner%20at%20CityVet%20in%20Charlotte%20Uptown.%20She%20adds%20that%20when%20given%20a%20texture%20they%20enjoy%2C%20cats%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20dig%20and%20fully%20cover%20their%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEasier%20to%20clean%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EClumping%20litter%20makes%20cleanup%20super%20easy%20because%20you%20can%20quickly%20remove%20solid%20and%20liquid%20clumps%20without%20leaving%20any%20waste%20behind.%20However%2C%20if%20daily%20scooping%20feels%20like%20a%20hassle%20or%20is%20physically%20difficult%2C%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-self-cleaning-litter-boxes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20automatic%20litter%20boxes%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20a%20great%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOdor%20control%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20clumps%20help%20trap%20odors%2C%20but%20any%20litter%20box%20will%20start%20to%20smell%20if%20it's%20not%20scooped%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2250c1c65a-273f-455f-9254-88dff633eccd%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Clumping%20cat%20litter%20cons%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EClumping%20cat%20litter%20cons%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDust%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAlmost%20any%20litter%20you%20buy%20will%20create%20some%20dust%20when%20poured%20or%20when%20your%20cat%20digs.%20This%20can%20cause%20irritation%20for%20both%20cats%20and%20humans%2C%20especially%20cats%20with%20respiratory%20issues%20such%20as%20asthma.%20Cahn%20says%20to%20take%20extra%20caution%20when%20purchasing%20clumping%20clay%20litter%2C%20as%20some%20can%20be%20especially%20dusty.%20We've%20tested%20and%20recommend%20two%20low-dust%20clumping%20clay%20options%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-74876-20%26h%3D73e2aee396ce3110ab67f33a27f8c6ed926a25f581ecf7aaa272c808ee8fe156%26postID%3D67d99499e45285883912df55%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Fclumping-vs-non-clumping-litter%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.chewy.com%252Ftidy-cats-naturally-strong-clumping%252Fdp%252F838870%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETidy%20Cats%20Naturally%20Strong%20Unscented%20Litter%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-74876-20%26h%3Dd6b077b9e293d0a964fe6d110d47843cdbb119403e1dd135bd53cd9d76da7141%26postID%3D67d99499e45285883912