d%2C%20observing%20that%20it%20was%20a%20combination%20of%20two%20arbitrary%20words%20-%20'Chuti'%20and%20'Ram'%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNone%20appeared%20observed%20and%20ordered%20that%20since%20this%20is%20the%20fourth%20hearing%20the%20instinct%20mark%20is%20a%20combination%20of%20two%20arbitrary%20words%20Chuti%20and%20ram%20and%20the%20instinct%20mark%20as%20a%20whole%20is%20distinctive%20and%20it%20can%20be%20differentiated%20from%20the%20person%20to%20others%20and%20the%20Instinct%20mark%20has%20no%20direct%20reference%20to%20the%20applied%20goods%2C%20hence%20objection%20u%2Fs%209%20waived%20and%20the%20mark%20accepted%2C%26quot%3B%20Senior%20Trademark%20Examiner%20Balaji%20said%20in%20the%20order.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20word%20has%20no%20direct%20reference%20to%20the%20goods%20that%20the%20company%20was%20selling%2C%20which%20were%20%3Cem%3E'namkeen'%3C%2Fem%3E%20(snacks)%20and%20biscuits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%209(2)(c)%20of%20the%20Trade%20Marks%20Act%20bars%20trademarks%20that%20are%20considered%20scandalous%2C%20obscene%2C%20or%20contrary%20to%20public%20morality.%20Words%20or%20phrases%20deemed%20vulgar%2C%20offensive%2C%20or%20inappropriate%20for%20public%20sensibilities%20cannot%20be%20approved%2C%20nor%20can%20trademarks%20that%20offend%20religious%20sentiments%20or%20are%20contrary%20to%20public%20order.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20trademark%20is%20said%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Baccepted%20%26amp%3B%20advertised%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20signals%20that%20the%20application%20has%20cleared%20the%20initial%20examination%20and%20the%20examiner%20either%20found%20no%20objections%20or%20resolved%20any%20concerns%20during%20scrutiny.%20The%20mark%20is%20then%20published%20in%20the%20Trademark%20Journal%2C%20allowing%20its%20review%2C%20which%2C%20in%20this%20case%2C%20was%20done%20on%20Monday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20acceptance%2C%20several%20experts%20questioned%20the%20review%20process%20and%20pointed%20out%20that%20registering%20terms%20that%20could%20be%20considered%20offensive%20could%20have%20legal%20implications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20acceptance%20was%20then%20withdrawn%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20with%20the%20Registry%20stating%20that%20an%20error%20had%20been%20made.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%2C%20the%20registry%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20above%20mentioned%20application%20has%20been%20accepted%20through%20an%20error.%20The%20registration%20of%20the%20mark%20submitted%20for%20registration%20is%20open%20to%20objection%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20the%20mark%20is%20not%20registration%20within%20the%20meaning%20of%20Section%209%20%2F%2011%20of%20the%20Trade%20Marks%20Act%2C%201999.%20The%20Registrar%20therefore%20proposes%20to%20withdraw%20the%20acceptance%20in%20pursuance%20of%20Section%2019%20of%20the%20Act%20read%20with%20Rule%2038%20of%20the%20Trade%20Marks%20rules%2C%202017%20and%20a%20hearing%20in%20respect%20of%20the%20application%20has%20been%20appointed%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20fail%20to%20attend%20the%20hearing%20the%20order%20of%20acceptance%20will%20be%20deemed%20to%20be%20withdrawn%20in%20pursuance%20of%20Section%2019%20of%20the%20Act%20read%20with%20rule%2038%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20stated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742308740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-06%2Fq43s9bf8_biscuits-generic_625x300_29_June_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftrademark-namkeen-trade-marks-registry-accepts-chutiyaram-for-biscuits-company-does-u-turn-7953341%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20weeks%20after%20it%20accepted%20an%20application%20for%20the%20registration%20of%20the%20word%20'Chutiyaram'%2C%20making%20many%20wonder%20whether%20it%20was%20in%20keeping%20with%20a%20section%20barring%20trademarks%20that%20are%20considered%20obscene%2C%20the%20Trade%20Marks%20Registry%20has%20done%20a%20U-turn.%22%2C%22a